[codex-monitored] heartbeat: elapsed=30s
codex
Static tracing shows the signature comparison precedes parsing, the equal-length guard short-circuits before `timingSafeEqual`, and duplicate lookup follows full shape validation. One concern is already visible: the implementation bypasses the required `express.json({ verify })` raw-byte mechanism by mounting `express.raw()` for `/webhook`; I’m now testing whether this is merely a constraint violation or also causes observable regressions.

Adversarial prediction: a first valid event will return exact 200 JSON; a second correctly signed, valid event with the same `id` but different `type`/`timestamp`/`data` will return exact 409 JSON based only on `id`. Separately, malformed JSON will return exact 401 with no signature and exact 400 with its valid signature—never HTML.
