codex
The in-process probe confirms the ordinary malformed and primitive cases produce the documented JSON. It also exposed a boundary failure: an empty, unframed request with the correct HMAC of zero bytes returns `401 invalid_signature`, because the raw parser skips it and line 41 refuses to compute the HMAC. I’m checking the other pre-route parser boundary—default body-size rejection—before final grading.
