{"id":"webhook-parser-preempts-signature","severity":"HIGH","rule_id":"spec.error-shape-ordering","file":"server/index.js","line":7,"message":"express.raw() rejects bodies over its default 100 KB limit before the route runs. A 102401-byte malformed body with a valid signature produced an unhandled entity.too.large 413, violating the requirement that every invalid-JSON body return exact 401/400 JSON after signature-first processing.","confidence":"high"}
{"id":"webhook-unframed-empty-body","severity":"HIGH","rule_id":"spec.invalid-body-response","file":"server/index.js","line":41,"message":"For an empty request without Content-Length or Transfer-Encoding, body-parser skips capture and req.body is not a Buffer, so the correct HMAC of zero bytes returns 401 invalid_signature instead of the required 400 invalid_body.","confidence":"high"}
{"id":"webhook-raw-parser-constraint","severity":"MEDIUM","rule_id":"design.unidiomatic-pattern","file":"server/index.js","line":7,"message":"The implementation mounts express.raw() and manually calls JSON.parse() rather than using the explicitly required express.json() verify-option capture. The verify callback on line 8 stores req.rawBody but that value is never used.","confidence":"high"}
